  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the training process is unaware of how its predictions are leveraged by the downstream task.",
    "Depending on how the training proceeds, the trained model can be either under-confident (high-variance) or overconfident(low-variance).",
    "For example, consider a scene where the actual d gt signifies a collision-free scenario.",
    "That is h(d gt) = -d gt + d 0 ≤ 0.",
    "Now, imagine that for this situation, the network of Fig. 4 predicts a µ θ (u, o) which is very close to d gt but the variance is unreasonably higher."
  ],
